@startuml Seq01_Authentication
!theme plain
participant User
participant "Browser/Frontend" as Frontend
participant "FastAPI Backend" as Backend
participant "JWT Manager" as JWT
participant "MySQL Database" as DB
participant "Password Hasher" as Hasher

autonumber

Note over User,DB: **REGISTRATION FLOW**

User -> Frontend: Click Register
Frontend -> Frontend: Display registration form
User -> Frontend: Enter name, email, password
Frontend -> Backend: POST /auth/register\n{name, email, password}

Backend -> Hasher: hash_password(password)
Hasher --> Backend: password_hash
Backend -> DB: INSERT INTO users\n(name, email, password_hash)
DB --> Backend: user_id

Backend -> JWT: generate_token(user_id)
JWT --> Backend: access_token, refresh_token
Backend --> Frontend: {user_id, access_token, refresh_token}

Frontend -> Frontend: Store tokens (localStorage/sessionStorage)
Frontend --> User: Redirect to login/dashboard
User --> Frontend: Registration success

Note over User,DB: **LOGIN FLOW**

User -> Frontend: Click Login
Frontend -> Frontend: Display login form
User -> Frontend: Enter email, password

Frontend -> Backend: POST /auth/login\n{email, password}

Backend -> DB: SELECT user WHERE email
DB --> Backend: user {id, password_hash}

Backend -> Hasher: verify_password(input_password, password_hash)
Hasher --> Backend: is_valid (true/false)

alt Password Valid
    Backend -> JWT: create_jwt_token(user_id, expiry)
    JWT --> Backend: access_token
    JWT --> Backend: refresh_token
    Backend --> Frontend: {access_token, refresh_token, user}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Store tokens
    Frontend --> User: Redirect to dashboard
else Password Invalid
    Backend --> Frontend: {error: "Invalid credentials"}
    Frontend --> User: Show error message
end

Note over User,DB: **ACCESS PROTECTED ROUTE**

User -> Frontend: Access dashboard
Frontend -> Frontend: Get token from storage
Frontend -> Backend: GET /dashboard\nHeader: Authorization: Bearer {token}

Backend -> JWT: verify_token(token)
alt Token Valid
    JWT --> Backend: {user_id, is_valid}
    Backend -> DB: SELECT user WHERE id=user_id
    DB --> Backend: user_data
    Backend -> Frontend: dashboard_data
    Frontend --> User: Display dashboard
else Token Expired
    JWT --> Backend: {error: "Token expired"}
    Backend -> JWT: refresh_token(refresh_token)
    JWT --> Backend: new_access_token
    Backend --> Frontend: {new_access_token}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Update stored token
    Frontend -> Backend: Retry request
else Token Invalid
    JWT --> Backend: {error: "Invalid token"}
    Backend --> Frontend: {error: "Unauthorized"}
    Frontend -> Frontend: Clear tokens
    Frontend --> User: Redirect to login
end

Note over User,DB: **LOGOUT FLOW**

User -> Frontend: Click Logout
Frontend -> Frontend: Clear tokens from storage
Frontend -> Backend: POST /auth/logout\nHeader: Authorization: Bearer {token}

Backend -> JWT: invalidate_token(token)
JWT --> Backend: {status: "logout success"}
Backend --> Frontend: {status: "logged out"}

Frontend -> Frontend: Clear user session
Frontend --> User: Redirect to login page

@enduml
